						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Ānanda, Bhādrapada śu. 11.</hi> On the basis of palaeography it may be assigned to the 17th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>Incomplete. It seems to refer to a gift of land below the tank Lingasamudram at Timmāpuram by Bejavāḍa Malli-vīrsāni.</p>						

						</summary>
